eFi\n  - The Future of GroDAO\n  - The Future of Gro Protocol\n- After episodes are completed, rest of funding ($1750 USDC) will be received\n\n#### Option 2: 2 Episode Series\n- Receive $650 USDC to the Podcast Network Pod Multi-sig\n  - Multi-sig will be a 3-of-5 consisting of 2 members from the Podcast Network Pod, 1 member from People Pod, and 2 members from the Gro DAO discord community at large\n- Finalise guests and topic order\n- Produce 2 episodes over the course of 2 months. Topics:\n  - The Future of Gro Protocol versus the future of DeFi\n  - Contributing to DAOs\n\n### Composition\nMiss Homie\n- BanklessDAO Contributor, GroDAO OG\n- Produced Podcast Series in 2017 - Tech Homie and Friends\n- Operations for Crypto Sapiens\n- Contributor to Podcast Hatchery\n\nEureka John\n- BanklessDAO Contribuor\n- Owner - [EurekaStreetCrypto](https://eurekastreetxyz.wordpress.com/)\n- Producer - Crypto Sapiens, Other Podcasts\n- Contributor - PodsDAO\n\nDeborah \n- GroDAO OG - Marketing\n\nMrrpiusz\n- GroDAO OG\n- Creative Designer - Arenaweb3\n- Twitter Operator - StafiProtocol\n\n## Pros\n- Increased outreach for the web3 community at large\n- Exposure to potential partnerships \n- Learning opportunities for gromies and for the web3 community at large\n- A new opportunities for interested community members to participate and contribute to the DAO\n- A chance for members who have left the project/protocol to see the upcoming growth of the project/dao/protocol, this is a way to promote web3 citizens to join the community and build awareness about Gro DAO, which is something that is desperately needed from responses given in the [GroDAO Sentiment Survey](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1kzI-DJDnlBtrAMqSA4xOYKArydM73zfSKjhcWtiQLQM/edit?usp=forms_home&ths=true)\n- Aligns with the mission of Gro DAO to make Web3 more accessible\n\n## Cons\n- Even though the series will have 10 episodes, this idea is a test. This series will be used to flesh out the idea of a podcast and help train members in GroDAO to produce podcasts in the community. While it is necessary to establish this process to help assist the cause, there is a potential that the test could fail to gain the traction intended for the outside community within the 10 episodes allotted.\n\n## Timeline & Voting\n-Vote 36 will run for 5 days and will follow the ranked-choice voting (instant runoff voting) format as there are 3 viable options to choose from. Accordingly, users can rank their choices in order of preference. If no option receives a majority share of votes (over 50%), the option with the least amount of votes will be eliminated, and those who voted for this option will have their second choice recorded instead.\n\nYou can read more about ranked-choice voting [here](https://docs.snapshot.org/user-guides/proposals/voting-types#ranked-choice-voting-instant-runoff-voting).\n\nIf vote 36 passes, the team will begin construction on the first episode, with a projected launch date of October 2nd. \n\nCommunity Members will have the opportunity to have their say on the topics of the episodes.  Suggestions are above, but you can be present your topic ideas in the ideas section of the Discord server.",
