      "title": "Vote 31: Emergency Multi-sig Signers Election",
      "content": "## Summary\nThis proposal calls for the election of emergency multi-sig signers for Gro DAO, which is integral for swift decision-making and executing on certain whitelisted actions in case of emergency (see to [GRFC Forum Post](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535) for full details).\n\nAs agreed in [Vote 27](https://vote.gro.xyz/#/proposal/0xdaa54ba4e9d3d789fb17369cc9c3783a0e424374a46bad601bf86d16532c70c2), the emergency multi-sig will comprise of 4 pod signers (1 from each pod) and 3 non-pod signers, making up a total of 7 signers. During the [call for applications](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535) only 1 member from each pod submitted an application:\n- [Jaypow](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535/3) (People Pod)\n- [KD](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535/4) (Groda Pod)\n- [Bernard](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535/10) (FiSt Pod)\n- [Wei.wang](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535/7) (Panda Pod)\n\nAs this meets the minimum pod-signer requirement, Vote 31 will only be taking into consideration the non-pod signer applications received, to fill the 3 remaining positions.\n\n## Voting Options\nVoting will be conducted via a multi-winner [weighted voting strategy](https://docs.snapshot.org/user-guides/proposals/voting-types#weighted-voting) on Snapshot, where the top 3 voted non-pod signers will be elected into the emergency multi-sig. DAO members can spread their voting power across any number of choices, being able to express support for as many candidates as they see fit and specify how much they support each candidate. It is advised, however, that DAO members do not express support for more than 3 candidates, and that they consider the requirements and responsibilities guidelines outlined in the [GRFC Forum Post](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535#requirements-responsibilities-7) when selecting candidates.\n\n### DAO members can vote on the following options:\n- [Organized Chaos](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535/5)\n  - Gro DAO Experience: OG Programme member and part of the DAO since 2021\n  - Qualifications: Has worked in crypto for 7 years with a focus on regulation and government, strong community engagement skills, analytical mindset, experienced in decentralised governance\n  - Time zone: UTC +2\n\n- [Ponmile](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535/8)\n  - Gro DAO Experience: OG Programme member and part of the DAO since  2022\n  - Qualifications: 2 years in crypto (community management and DAO tooling experience)\n  - Time zone: UTC +1\n\n- [Deborah](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535/9)\n  - Gro DAO Experience: OG Programme member (marketing team), G-Force member and part the DAO since 2022\n  - Qualifications: 3 years in crypto (content development, ambassadorship, community moderation and growth)\n  - Time zone: UTC +1\n\n- [RSKL](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535/11)\n  - Gro DAO Experience: OG and part of the DAO since 2021\n  - Qualifications: 8 years in crypto and 4 years working in crypto\n  - Time zone: UTC +7\n\n- **Reject all candidates**\n\n## Implementation\nIf Vote 31 is passed, the emergency multi-sig will be set up in the following week(s), with the righftul candidates set up as signers (4 pod members and 3 non-pod members) in a 4-of-7 multi-sig configuration, for a period of 6 months.\n\nSigners who are unable to meet [expectations](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-call-for-applications-emergency-multi-sig-signers-election-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-3/535#requirements-responsibilities-7) can resign from the role or be voted out by the emergency multi-sig committee or be voted out by the DAO via Snapshot vote. If a signer is voted out, an interim emergency multi-sig signer will be elected by the remaining emergency multi-sig signers, until a new signer is formally elected by the DAO via Snapshot.\n\n## Pros\n- Enhances security, rapid decision-making, and execution of whitelisted actions in case of emergencies\n- Ensures decentralisation by including representatives from each pod as well as non-pod members (the Gro DAO community)\n- Promotes transparency and efficiency in Gro DAO operations\n\n## Cons\n- Based on availability, it is possible that some signers may not be able to act as swiftly as desired in all situations\n\n## Budget\nThe elected non-pod members will receive a stipend of 500 $USDC and 1000 GRO each month, assuming they retain their role for the duration of the 6-month term. This equates to a total of $9,000 USDC + 18,000 GRO for the 6-month term.\n\nThere will also be a negligible amount of Eth sent from the DAO treasury that will be used to cover gas fees.\n\n## Timeline\nVote 31 will run for 5 days on a weighted voting basis, during which DAO members have the opportunity to spread their voting power across their preferred candidate(s).\n\nIf Vote 31 is passed (i.e. the top 3 voted for options are candidates), the emergency multi-sig will be set up and configured accordingly.\n\nIf Vote 31 isn’t passed (i.e. the ‘reject all candidates’ option is one of the top 3 voted for options, or quorum isn't met), there will be another push for suitable emergency multi-sig signers from the community to fill up the remaining spaces.\n\n6 months after the set up of the emergency multi-sig, there will be another election to determine the emergency multi-sig signers for the following term.",
