      "title": "Vote 26: Require GRO tokens to be locked to vote, and define off-chain governance processes",
      "content": "# Summary\n\nFor Gro DAO to become more robust, trustless and decentralised, it should move towards on-chain governance.\n\nTo do so, it must first ensure that its long-term interests are aligned with those of its members. This can be done by ***only allowing locked GRO tokens (i.e. [vesting tokens](https://medium.com/gro-protocol/gro-rewards-and-vesting-737c6d34113e) that are still not vested) to vote***. In other words, it is being proposed that a DAO member can only participate in DAO governance if they lock up the tokens they wish to use towards voting, in a [vesting contract](https://etherscan.io/address/0x748218256AfE0A19a88EBEB2E0C5Ce86d2178360#readContract).\n\nThe DAO should also agree on what requires DAO governance, and in particular, ***ratify what should be governed by who***. [This table](https://www.notion.so/grodao/What-is-Governed-by-Who-2329c150fbed4068906e18d49b14ae58) illustrates what is currently governed and executed by who, and proposes how this should look in a future where on-chain governance is approved by the DAO. It is worth noting that even if and when automatic on-chain governance execution is enabled, not all actions can or should be configured for automated execution immediately.\n\nIt is also important to ***ratify the off-chain governance process***. This will cover the steps to raise and vote on a proposal when only vesting GRO counts towards votes and where on-chain governance cannot be used to implement the resulting actions (either because it is not approved by the DAO or because the respective proposal would not result in an on-chain action, as illustrated in [this table](https://www.notion.so/grodao/What-is-Governed-by-Who-2329c150fbed4068906e18d49b14ae58)). In such instances, this proposed [off-chain governance process](https://www.notion.so/grodao/Off-Chain-Governance-Process-31d5b29d639847a496d54ce762f7391c) would be used:\n\n1. Discuss in Discord at #governance channel\n2. Write a Gro Request For Comments (GRFC) on [Gro DAO Forum](http://community.gro.xyz/), following these [guidelines](https://www.notion.so/GRO-Request-For-Comments-GRFC-Forum-Post-Template-95908b4098034f8a8133ec10332458ea) on writing GRFCs, and use the poll feature to conduct an informal signalling vote\n3. After at least **[6 days]** of GRFC, if feedback has been implemented and there is a general consensus (as determined by GRFC feedback and by at least **[15 members]** participating in a passing signalling vote) that the proposal should be taken to vote, addresses with **[175,000+ vesting or delegated vesting GRO tokens]** (~0.5% of circulating GRO Supply), or whitelisted addresses; can initiate the proposal on Gro DAO’s [Snapshot](http://vote.gro.xyz/), using this [Proposal Description Template](https://www.notion.so/Proposal-Template-4435c485d68844dfb736d06429043d85)\n4. The vote would be live for at least **[5 days]** for off-chain voting on Snapshot, and would need to meet a quorum of **[350,000 vesting GRO]** (~1% of circulating GRO Supply) and a passing rate of over **[50%]**\n5. A successful vote would have **[3 days]** of timelock for implementation (if applicable), allowing time for emergency multi-sig to act if there’s a malicious attack\n\n![image](ipfs://bafkreibfdbq5yiqdmldua5itftycc5jmby337s5plgf3ra2os4ulkyw6wa)\n***A full in-depth description of this proposal can be found [here](https://community.gro.xyz/t/grfc-require-gro-tokens-to-be-locked-to-vote-and-define-off-chain-governance-processes-meta-governance-update-sub-proposal-1/528).***\n\n# Explanation of each voting option\nThis proposal marks the initial step in a multi-step meta-governance update for Gro DAO. It proposes to:\n- Allow only locked GRO tokens (i.e. vesting tokens that are still not vested) to vote;\n- Ratify what should be governed by who, and;\n- Ratify off-chain governance process\n\nAccordingly, DAO members can either vote:\n- FOR: approve the proposal\n- AGAINST: do not approve the proposal\n- ABSTAIN: no opinion on this proposal\n\n# Implementation\n***On-chain action:*** allow only locked GRO tokens (i.e. vesting tokens that are still not vested) to vote, by setting the voting weight for liquid GRO on the [vote aggregator contract](https://etherscan.io/address/0x156d9aaD5975Ec9Aa9E2C621F408C8469D0D6953#readContract) to 0.\n\n***Off-chain action:*** Ratify (the current and proposed distinctions of) [what should be governed by who](https://www.notion.so/grodao/What-is-Governed-by-Who-2329c150fbed4068906e18d49b14ae58), as documented.\n\n***Off-chain action:*** Ratify [off-chain governance process](https://www.notion.so/grodao/Off-Chain-Governance-Process-31d5b29d639847a496d54ce762f7391c), as documented, by:\n- Changing Snapshot proposal threshold from 1,000,000 to 175,000 GRO\n- Changing Snapshot quorum from 50,000 to 350,000 GRO\n\n***Off-chain action:*** Add the [with-delegation](https://docs.snapshot.org/user-guides/delegation) strategy to the Gro DAO Snapshot space.\n\n# Benefits (Pros)\n\nAllow only locked GRO tokens (i.e. vesting tokens that are still not vested) to vote:\n- Greater alignment between the DAO and its members\n- Further incentivises longer-term commitments to the DAO\n- Reduced risk of governance attack ahead of on-chain governance implementation which enables the Snapshot proposal threshold to be reduced (from 1,000,000 to 175,000 vesting GRO)\n\nRatify what should be governed by who:\n- Greater clarity on current and future governance processes\n- Further streamlining of DAO operations\n- Provides context for forthcoming meta-governance update proposals\n\nRatify off-chain governance process:\n- Greater clarity on off-chain governance process\n- Easier to meet proposal and quorum thresholds, and increase total voter participation by enabling voter delegation\n\n# Downsides (Cons)\n- Greater operational overhead\n- More complicated processes that need to be understood by DAO members\n- Higher quorum threshold (350,000 GRO) to be met for future proposals to be passed on Snapshot\n- Gas fees required to lock GRO tokens and to claim vesting rewards\n\n# Next Steps\n\nThis vote will run for 5 days on a simple majority basis.\n\nIf the proposal is not passed, the People Pod will carefully review the proposal and engage in a thorough dialogue with the community to incorporate any further feedback received.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n",
