ackend & smart contracts)\n- LH (backend)\n- WW (backend)\n- Kwww (product manager)\n- VW (full-stack)\n- YQ (designer)\n\nThese contributors have experience building products and tooling across multiple DeFi protocols on multiple chains (Ethereum, Avalanche, Polygon, Optimism, and Arbitrum) and will utilise their collective experiences to lower the barrier to utilising the Gro protocol. \n\nFor the next 6 months (13 February 2023 - 13 August 2023), the proposed budget is 300,000 USDC + 150,000 GRO (as detailed in the [Community Forum](https://community.gro.xyz/t/panda-product-pod-proposal/458/12)) that will be transferred to the Panda Product Pod's operational wallet if approved. Any unused budget will be returned to the DAO Treasury at the end of the 6 months.\n\nThe operational wallet will be a 3-of-5 multi-sig wallet consisting of 2 Panda Product Pod contributors, 2 People Pod contributors, and 1 Groda Pod contributor.\n\n## Reporting\nPanda Product Pod will update the DAO on its progress via quarterly reports and regularly through the community channels such as Community Forum, Discord, and Telegram. \n\n## Next Steps\nThis vote will run for 5 days on a simple majority basis.\n\n",
