      "content": "_TLDR: This proposal sets out selected Convex strategies for whitelist and approval for use in Gro protocol_\n\nOriginal community forum post here: https://community.gro.xyz/t/vote-015-gro-protocol-strategy-selection-whitelist/296\n\n### Background and summary\n\n* Over the past week there has been significant losses incurred by Vault users as part of the UST de-peg\n* There will be a future post-mortem on this separately, including discussion around risk management and possible compensation options\n* As an urgent priority however we should confirm whether the DAO is comfortable with the current strategies in place, together with new proposed strategies to replace UST\n\n### Vote 015H:  Whitelist TUSD-3CRV Convex strategy for use in Gro protocol\n\nGro protocol has been designed to use [Convex pool strategies](https://blog.gro.xyz/gro-new-vault-pwrd-87c3ec018da9) following [Gro DAO Vote 009](https://vote.gro.xyz/#/proposal/0x7e6a526031028514cf78fb8618a65d1cc71d457549f8c1b8180a96443d741428). All these strategies pair 3CRV with a different stablecoin.\n\nThat means each strategy has full exposure to each of the 3CRV assets plus whichever stablecoin is also in the pool. As we saw with UST wormhole, if any of the assets moves off-peg then this results in a loss for the strategy as a whole.\n\nProposal that Gro DAO approves **TUSD-3CRV** Convex strategy for use in Gro protocol with (1) a maximum Vault exposure of 50% and (2) a stop-loss in place in case of significant de-peg (future DAO vote to decide on exact parameters for this). \n\n### More information on TUSD\n\n* Created by TrustToken and backed 1:1 by fiat collateral\n* Live for 50 months with a DeFi Safety score of 84% (for TrueFi) and a market cap of $1.22bn\n* Read more here: [https://www.trusttoken.com/products](https://www.trusttoken.com/products)\n* Link to pool: [Curve.fi](https://curve.fi/tusd) (pool depth: $80m as at 17th May)\n* Current Convex yield **2.57%** (as at 17 May)\n\n### Voting process\n\n**FOR**: Approve the strategy for whitelist on Gro protocol\n**AGAINST**: Do not approve the strategy for whitelist on Gro protocol\n**ABSTAIN**: No opinion on approving this strategy for whitelist on Gro protocol \n\n### Next steps\n\nThis vote will run for **3 days**.\n\nEach strategy that receives majority approval (ignoring abstain votes) will be added to the protocol whitelist, meaning there is DAO authority to allocate protocol funds (within the maximum Vault exposures).\n\nFuture strategies can be suggested and voted on by the DAO, and at any time community members can also propose a removal of a strategy from the current whitelist.",
